        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Extended Description</title>
            <para>Power is always supplied to the reverse motion sensor on pin 1 from fuse #29.</para>
            <para>When the transmission is shifted into reverse, voltage is supplied to pin 3 from fuse F20. The reverse
                motion sensor will then sound the back-up alarm.
            </para>
            <para>When the reverse motion sensor detects reverse motion on the drivetrain, voltage will be supplied on
                pin 2 to sound the back-up alarm.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
